  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries worldwide. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key aspects of AML regulations typically include:\n\n1. Financial reporting requirements\n2. Customer due diligence\n3. Transaction monitoring\n4. Suspicious activity reporting\n5. Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\nIn the United States, key AML regulations include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. Many other countries have similar laws, and international organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) help coordinate global AML efforts.",
